# docs/ai trust tiers (agents)

When inferring **what to build next**, **what is unfinished**, or **current behavior**, follow this rule. Full policy: `docs/ai/templates/DOC_GOVERNANCE.md` §5.3; human-edited backlog: `docs/ai/ACTIVE_WORK.md`.

## Tier A — planning sources (may drive work)

- `docs/ai/PROJECT_CONTEXT.md`
- `docs/ai/PROGRESS_LOG.md` (recent entries only)
- `docs/ai/BOOTSTRAP_DIGEST.md`
- `docs/ai/ACTIVE_WORK.md` (authoritative short backlog when present)
- `docs/ai/FEATURE_REGISTRY.md` — only **In Progress** or **Planned** rows
- `docs/ai/TECH_DEBT.md` — only **Open** rows
- `docs/design/Overview.md` + `docs/design/systems/*.md` — **read-only** for agents
- `卡牌游戏.md` — stub only; do not treat as content source
- A **single** in-repo design doc the user names for the current task, if Meta **Status** is `In Progress` or `Review`

## Tier B — reference only (do not build backlog from)

- Roadmaps / plans with Meta **Done**, **Deferred**, **Cancelled**, **Archived**, **Snapshot**, or **Reference**
- `*_CURRENT_STATE.md` snapshots
- Unchecked checkboxes or “待做” prose in Tier B docs
- `docs/ai/sessions/` (session notes)
- Unscoped ideas in design docs — **not** mandatory work unless in ACTIVE_WORK

Allowed use: naming, architecture context, links — **not** “must implement because doc says so”.

## Tier C — code is truth

If Tier A/B disagrees with **source code** or **tests / `npm run verify`**:

1. Trust **code + tests** for “what exists today”.
2. State that the doc may be stale; do not treat gaps as mandatory work unless user or ACTIVE_WORK asks.
3. Do not quote CLI/API from old docs without verifying in repo.

## Conflicts

| Situation | Resolution |
|-----------|------------|
| Doc vs code | Code (+ tests) |
| Doc vs user this session | User |
| ACTIVE_WORK vs old roadmap | ACTIVE_WORK |
| Design doc vs in-repo impl spec | `docs/design/systems/*` for **what**; in-repo for **how**; user resolves conflicts |
| FEATURE_REGISTRY Planned vs no ACTIVE_WORK entry | Ask user or treat as optional future |

## New work

Register in `FEATURE_REGISTRY.md`; update `ACTIVE_WORK.md` when user wants agent-visible priority. Do not start large implementation until user calls for it after design phase.
